            "arabicMeaning": "يقتحم / يدخل بالقوة",
            "synonyms": [
                "burgle",
                "force entry into"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "Thieves tried to "
                },
                {
                    "text": "break into",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " our house last night, but our loud dog scared them away"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Crime-related phrasal verb. Different from 'break in' (to wear something new until comfortable) or 'break down' (to stop working). Noun form: break-in (a burglary)."
        },
        {
            "word": "arrive",
            "wordType": "verb",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "To reach a "
